You are working on SUBIDHA CORE – Lucky Plan EMI System.

Goal:
Implement admin-only Settlement Import / Detail UI so staff can operate Bank Statement Import and UPI Settlement Import evidence from the webapp.

This phase is frontend UI + existing API integration only.

Do not implement auto-matching.
Do not implement suggested matching.
Do not change allocation validation.
Do not change reconciliation checks.
Do not mutate Payment, ReceiptDocument, MoneyMovement, JournalEntry, FinanceAccount, CashCounter, or source records.

Context:
Completed:
- L0 settlement schema foundation.
- L1 admin-only bank/UPI import parser endpoints.
- L2 admin-only manual SettlementAllocation APIs.
- Allocation-backed Reconciliation Control Tower checks.

Existing APIs:
- POST/GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/bank-imports/
- GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/bank-imports/{id}/
- GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/bank-imports/{id}/lines/
- POST/GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/upi-imports/
- GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/upi-imports/{id}/
- GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/upi-imports/{id}/lines/
- GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/allocations/
- POST /api/v1/admin/settlements/allocations/
- GET /api/v1/admin/settlements/allocations/{id}/
- POST /api/v1/admin/settlements/allocations/{id}/void/

Strict constraints:
- Do not change backend unless a real API contract mismatch is found.
- Do not add new APIs unless strictly required.
- Do not change payment posting.
- Do not change receipt generation.
- Do not change accounting posting.
- Do not change finance account behavior.
- Do not change cashier collection behavior.
- Do not auto-match payments.
- Do not suggest matches.
- Do not create reconciliation items from the UI.
- Do not close reconciliation items from the UI.
- Admin-only access.
- Do not expose settlement UI to customer/partner/vendor/cashier.
- Do not run bash scripts/run-release-candidate.sh.

